The name of the first \add is\add* Pison: that \add is\add*
it which compasseth the whole land of Havilah, where \add there is\add*
gold;

And the \nd LORD\nd* God caused a deep sleep to fall upon
Adam, and he slept: and he took one of his ribs, and closed up the
flesh instead thereof;

Of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female;
to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth.\f + \fr 7.3  \ft by sevens: Heb. seven
seven\f*

In the selfsame day entered Noah, and Shem, and Ham, and Japheth,
the sons of Noah, and Noah’s wife, and the three wives of his sons
with them, into the ark;

And God remembered Noah, and every living thing, and all the
cattle that \add was\add* with him in the ark: and God made a wind
to pass over the earth, and the waters asswaged;

And he went on his journeys from the south even to Beth-el,
unto the place where his tent had been at the beginning, between
Beth-el and Hai;

And it came to pass in the days of Amraphel king of Shinar,
Arioch king of Ellasar, Chedorlaomer king of Elam, and Tidal king
of nations;

With Chedorlaomer the king of Elam, and with Tidal king of
nations, and Amraphel king of Shinar, and Arioch king of Ellasar;
four kings with five.

¶ And there came one that had escaped, and told Abram the Hebrew;
for he dwelt in the plain of Mamre the Amorite, brother of Eshcol,
and brother of Aner: and these \add were\add* confederate with Abram.\f + \fr 14.13 
\ft plain: Heb. plains\f*

And he said unto Abram, Know of a surety that thy seed shall be a
stranger in a land \add that is\add* not theirs, and shall serve
them; and they shall afflict them four hundred years;

And as for Ishmael, I have heard thee: Behold, I have blessed
him, and will make him fruitful, and will multiply him exceedingly;
twelve princes shall he beget, and I will make him a great nation.

And there came two angels to Sodom at even; and Lot sat in the
gate of Sodom: and Lot seeing \add them\add* rose up to meet them; and he
bowed himself with his face toward the ground;

And Abraham took the wood of the burnt offering, and laid \add it\add*
upon Isaac his son; and he took the fire in his hand, and a knife;
and they went both of them together.

¶ And it came to pass after these things, that it was told
Abraham, saying, Behold, Milcah, she hath also born children unto thy
brother Nahor;

Behold, I stand by the well of water; and it shall come to pass, that when the
virgin cometh forth to draw \add water\add*, and I say to her, Give
me, I pray thee, a little water of thy pitcher to drink;

And his sons Isaac and Ishmael buried him in the cave of Machpelah,
in the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, which \add is\add*
before Mamre;

Sojourn in this land, and I will be with thee, and will bless
thee; for unto thee, and unto thy seed, I will give all these countries,
and I will perform the oath which I sware unto Abraham thy father;

And I will make thy seed to multiply as the stars of heaven,
and will give unto thy seed all these countries; and in thy seed
shall all the nations of the earth be blessed;

And Jacob said unto his father, I \add am\add* Esau thy firstborn;
I have done according as thou badest me: arise, I pray thee, sit
and eat of my venison, that thy soul may bless me.

And by thy sword shalt thou live, and shalt serve thy brother;
and it shall come to pass when thou shalt have the dominion, that thou shalt
break his yoke from off thy neck.

If thou shalt afflict my daughters, or if thou shalt take
\add other\add* wives beside my daughters, no man \add is\add* with us;
see, God \add is\add* witness betwixt me and thee.

Then Jacob was greatly afraid and distressed: and he divided
the people that \add was\add* with him, and the flocks, and herds,
and the camels, into two bands;

And God said unto him, I \add am\add* God Almighty: be fruitful
and multiply; a nation and a company of nations shall be of thee, and
kings shall come out of thy loins;

Esau took his wives of the daughters of Canaan; Adah the daughter
of Elon the Hittite, and Aholibamah the daughter of Anah the daughter
of Zibeon the Hivite;

For their riches were more than that they might dwell together;
and the land wherein they were strangers could not bear them because
of their cattle.

¶ And these \add are\add* the sons of Aholibamah Esau’s wife;
duke Jeush, duke Jaalam, duke Korah: these \add were\add* the dukes
\add that came\add* of Aholibamah the daughter of Anah, Esau’s wife.

But he refused, and said unto his master’s wife, Behold, my
master wotteth not what \add is\add* with me in the house, and he hath
committed all that he hath to my hand;

And there shall arise after them seven years of famine; and all the
plenty shall be forgotten in the land of Egypt; and the famine shall
consume the land;

Now therefore when I come to thy servant my father, and the
lad \add be\add* not with us; seeing that his life is bound up in the lad’s
life;

And Joseph said unto his brethren, and unto his father’s house,
I will go up, and shew Pharaoh, and say unto him, My brethren, and my
father’s house, which \add were\add* in the land of Canaan, are come unto me;

Cursed \add be\add* their anger, for \add it was\add* fierce;
and their wrath, for it was cruel: I will divide them in Jacob, and
scatter them in Israel.

¶ All these \add are\add* the twelve tribes of Israel: and this
\add is it\add* that their father spake unto them, and blessed them;
every one according to his blessing he blessed them.
